  Back in my other "mark" resto days I had all my engine tin powder coated
by Olympic Powder coating in Santa Ana, cali. They had (have) a color called
RONNIE BLACK, it was a color they developed to powder coat engine tin to
CONCOURS spec (accepted in concours judgeing). I am sure that they still
have this color available as most So Cal VW and the other "mark" people
still use them. Just ask for engine tin black.

ronnie

